  <span id="freeText1580479137996122755" style="display:none">Robert Reich explains the political agenda of America's "radcons" (radical conservatives), how they have seized power, how they have influenced national politics, and how this has affected the economy. Published in 2004, it describes the dilemma that we are still in, although we are now in the aftermath of the Bush administration that represented the worst of it. Obama is not mentioned, but Reich anticipated that Republican abuse of power would inevitably provoke discontent and a change in political direction, which he predicted would be influenced by a tradition of liberal thinking.</span>
